    "where f Trans (z) is the Transformer model, f DNN,Q, f DNN,K, f DNN,V are three DNN models.",
    "Sim(⋅, ⋅) is a similarity function.",
    "Latest WPP studies have explored the performance of Transformer-based models, such as the Informer (Zhou et al. 2021; Nascimento et al. 2023; Huang et al. 2022), Autoformer (Wu et al. 2021), Pyraformer (Liu et al. 2021b), and Fedformer (Zhou et al. 2022a, b; Deng et al. 2022).",
    "Studies observed that the transformer-based models could improve WPP efficiency by sampling a set of informative queries and keys with incorporating signal processing methods.",
    "Additionally, the DLinear model (Zeng et al. 2023) reported the performance improvement of WPPs through a simpler attention scheme."
